# Cloudflare Pages serves real static files BEFORE evaluating any rules,
# so /sitemap.xml, /robots.txt, /og.webp, /site.webmanifest etc. are served
# as themselves — no exact-match shenanigans needed (unlike nginx).
#
# SPA fallback for client-side routes (`/editor`, etc.) is handled
# natively by Cloudflare Pages when the Vite framework preset is detected:
# any path without a matching file gets `/index.html` with a 200 response.
#
# We intentionally do NOT include `/* /index.html 200` here — Cloudflare's
# `_redirects` parser flags it as an infinite loop (because their `.html`
# auto-stripper rewrites `/index.html` → `/index` → matches `/*` → loop)
# and ignores the rule, leaving us reliant on the auto-fallback anyway.
#
# If the auto-fallback ever stops working, the recovery is a tiny Pages
# Function at `functions/[[catchall]].ts` that re-fetches `/index.html`
# for non-asset 404s. We don't need that yet.
